        <name>3.4.1.9 Use a graph to solve simultaneous</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use graphs to solve the following pairs of simultaneous equations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;\[{@sysl1[1,1]@}={@sysr1[1,1]@}, \quad (eq1)\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[{@sysl1[2,1]@}={@sysr1[2,1]@}, \quad (eq2)\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By rearranging into the standrd form for tte equation of a straight line we get:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\( eq1: \quad y= \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\( eq2: \quad y = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By drawing the graphs we find that the two lines intersect at the point:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;\({@B1@}=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]&lt;/div&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;We are given the equations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[{@sysl1[1,1]@}={@sysr1[1,1]@}, \quad (eq1)\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[{@sysl1[2,1]@}={@sysr1[2,1]@}, \quad (eq2)\]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By rearranging into the standrd form for tte equation of a straight line we get:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\( eq1: \quad y= {@eq1@}\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\( eq2: \quad y = {@eq2@}\) &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now we draw the graphs of the two lines:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;{@plot([eq1, eq2], [x,-1,s1+3], grid2d, [yx_ratio, 1],[legend, true] )@}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We find that the two lines intersect at the point:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;\({@B1@}= {@ta@}\)&lt;/div&gt;</generalfeedback>
